Following is a table showing global passenger
traffic at airports around the world from the  Airports Council International 
(ACI) in  Montreal .  ACI gathers figures from over 1600 member airports in 175 countries. The
CHART compares ACI cargo (BLUE Line), and ACI passenger traffic (GRAY line).  Note: Total figures take into account international plus domestic passengers  plus direct transit passengers counted once.  Results are based on participating airports which make up about 70% of  traffic worldwide.   Source: Airports Council International  To contact the reporter on this story:
